div1.p: JUDGMENT ROLL
In re application No. 3482 for Writ H.C. of Kunijiro Toguchi
Witness my hand and official seal this 2nd day of Jan., 1917. Frank L. Crosby
United States District Court. WESTERN DISTRICT OF WASHINGTON.
HABEAS CORPUS
The President of the United States of America To Henry M. White, United States Commissioner of Immigration.

Greeting: We Command You, that you have the body of Kunijiro Toguchi by you imprisoned and detained, as it is said, together with the time and cause of such imprisonment and detention, by whatsoever name said Kunijiro Toguchi shall be called or charged, before the Hon. Jeremiah Neterer, United States District Judge for the Western District of Washington, at Seattle, Washington, in the Northern Division of said Western District of Washington, on the 16th day of December, 1916, ten o'clock in the fore noon, to do and receive what shall then and there be considered concerning the said Kunijiro Toguchi. And have you then and there this writ.

WITNESS the Hon. Jeremiah Neterer, Judge of the United States District Court for the Western District of Washington, this 11th day of December, in the year of our Lord one thousand nine hundred and sixteen.
Frank L. Crosby, Clerk.
By Edm Laken Deputy Clerk.
Form No. 282. RETURN ON SERVICE OF WRIT. United States of America, Western DISTRICT OF Washington } SS:

I hereby certify and return that I served the annexed Writ of Habeas Corpus & Order for Writ of Habeas Corpus, on the therein-named Henry M. White, U.S. Commissioner of Immigration, by handing to and leaving a true and correct copy thereof with Him personally at Seattle Wash. in said District on the 12th, day of December, A.D. 1916
John M. Boyle. U.S. Marshal.
Marshal's Fees $4.12
By Edward Williams Deputy.
ORIGINAL
United States District Court. Western DISTRICT OF WASHINGTON.
In the Matter of the Application of Kunijiro Toguchi For Writ of Habeas Corpus.
Habeas Corpus.
Let the within Writ issue.
James Kiefer, Attorney for Petitioner.
FILED IN THIS U.S. District Court, Western Dist. of Washington, NORTHERN DIVISION DEC 12 1916 FRANK L. CROSBY, Clerk, Edm Laken Deputy
